    "body": "## R1 prevention and public-surface audit\n\nThis draft PR hardens the AI forensics privacy boundary against foreign-machine home-directory paths, adds a deterministic read-only public-surface audit, extends regression coverage, and documents the R1/R2 boundary.\n\nKnown historical finding: category `home-path`; ref `origin/main`; commit `efd2a0e41da683bd3479182d996e6838a87c5fa7`; blob `293e93d832059d9424e17f96dd6f469de063a4ff`; repository-relative path `forensics/ai-runs/S6-ALPHA-FAIL-EVIDENCE-20260717T000000Z.md`; safe line `17`; fingerprint `sha256:2ed0ca4b0d5fd92edf40476702824acb06ceb34cd47f9080714609844e8673a7`.\n\nThe same blob finding is deduplicated across reachable history. `origin/forensics/ai-runs` has no matching finding in the current authorized forensic surface. Issue `#224` was read-only audited and contains no matching raw private-home finding.\n\nR1 does not rewrite history, mutate Issue `#224`, or publish a forensic package. R2 requires separate explicit authorization, verified backups, complete remote-ref inventory, collaborator coordination, and post-rewrite GitHub cache/support handling.\n\nValidation: Python compilation, 42 forensics unit tests, repository validator, diff check, synthetic clean/contaminated audit fixtures, and real authorized-ref audit.",
